revision.text:
'''{{nihongo|Nagata Shrine|長田神社,|Nagata-jinja}}''' is a [[Shinto]] [[Jinja (Shinto)|shrine]] in Nagata Ward, [[Kobe]], [[Japan]].
According to ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'', Nagata Shrine was founded by the [[Jingu of Japan|Empress Jing&#363;]] at the beginning of the [[3rd century]] CE along with [[Hirota Shrine]], dedicated to [[Amaterasu]], [[Sumiyoshi Taisha]] and [[Ikuta Shrine]], dedicated to the [[kami]] Wakahirume.
{{Shinto-stub}}
{{coor title dms|34|40|17|N|135|08|49|E|region:JP-28_type:landmark_source:dewiki}}
[[Category:3rd century establishments]] [[Category:Shinto shrines]] [[Category:Shinto shrines in Hyōgo Prefecture]]
